Tyrael intensified his shield of light as more and more shots came at him.

Tyrael: Fools! Hydras, you do not even have the guts to fight me like
the leader you pretend to be!  Would you risk all the credibility you
have in front of your crew?  Will you prove yourself weak?

He sent eight light spears at his nemesis.

Dreadplague, on her part, could not dodge the shots from Perceptor. No
matter, she struck twice at the Predacons, not worrying about her own
wounds. She also brought more and more fear in the mind of her opponent.

The Dragoon, though, saw that things were going quite well. Even
though in smaller number, the Tripredacus were fighting well. It was
his time now to push the Predacons back.

He looked for a good target. He found it in Thrust, Terpa and
Bumblebee, and fired a massive fireball at the group.
